## Quality Assurance

### Content Quality Checklist

**Before Publishing Any Content**:

**Voice & Tone**:

- [ ] Conversational and approachable
- [ ] Professional credibility maintained
- [ ] Humour enhances, doesn't distract
- [ ] Pop culture references explained
- [ ] Canadian English spelling throughout
- [ ] No forbidden terminology used

**Structure**:

- [ ] Clear purpose stated upfront
- [ ] Logical flow of ideas
- [ ] Appropriate heading levels
- [ ] Scannable with headers and short paragraphs
- [ ] Call to action or clear conclusion

**Content**:

- [ ] No buzzword bingo or unnecessary jargon
- [ ] "Business capability" not just "capability"
- [ ] Concrete examples for abstract concepts
- [ ] Shows, doesn't just tell
- [ ] Acknowledges trade-offs and limitations

**Technical Accuracy**:

- [ ] ArchiMate terms used correctly
- [ ] TOGAF references accurate
- [ ] Domain terminology precise
- [ ] No contradictions with prior content
- [ ] Sources cited where applicable

**Brand Alignment**:

- [ ] Reflects "influence through expertise"
- [ ] Makes others more successful
- [ ] Embraces "good enough"
- [ ] Stays relevant to audience needs
- [ ] Visual identity applied correctly

